-- Mexico PRD Names Mancera as Candidate for Mexico City Mayor Race
-- B y   A d r i a n a   L o p e z   C a r a v e o
-- 2012-01-20T00:56:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/mexico-prd-names-mancera-as-candidate-for-mexico-city-mayor-race.html
Mexico ’s  Party of the Democratic
Revolution , or PRD, selected Miguel Angel Mancera as its
candidate for Mexico City mayor.  Mancera, who served as the capital’s top prosecutor under
current Mayor Marcelo Ebrard, won a referendum held from Jan. 14
to Jan. 16, the party said an at event in Mexico City broadcast
by Milenio TV.  Mancera will compete against Isabel Miranda de Wallace, a
security activist, who will run for the post with President
Felipe Calderon’s  National Action Party .  The  Institutional Revolutionary Party , known as the PRI,
hasn’t designated its candidate for the July 1 election.  The PRD has governed the nation’s capital for fourteen
years.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adriana Lopez Caraveo in Mexico City at 
 adrianalopez@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
